Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, chop the @sweet potato{1%unit} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the sweet potato chunks onto a large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{},
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender and golden,
~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}, then pop
half of them into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{80%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot,
add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and fry until starting to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the black beans (whole and mashed), @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add
less if you'd prefer things milder), @vegetable stock paste{10%grams},
@sugar{1%tsp} and @water{150%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until all the liquid has evaporated,
~{8-10%minutes}.

Once cooked, stir the roasted sweet potato through the chorizo mixture.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6%units} onto a lightly oiled baking tray and
spoon the bean mixture onto one half of each one. Sprinkle over cheese. Fold
the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Rub a little @oil{} over the top of each one, then bake on the top shelf until
golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once golden, transfer the quesadillas to your plates.

Serve with a dollop of @soured cream{75%grams} and the chips alongside.

Enjoy!